dreamzzt (3.0.8) stable; urgency=low

  * Sound support for Dreamcast
  * Support STK-colored torches, ammo, energizers
  * Uses system clock for improved game timing
  * Game speed and volume can be adjusted from title screen
  * Integration with the Trac ticket system for in-game bug reports
  * Mission:Enigma is now completable 

  * Centipede segments harm player (#23)
  * Centipedes could become disconnected if shot by an enemy (#27)
  * Board transitions may not work properly after saving (#39)
  * Change object search order to match ZZT (#13)
  * Support stat-less objects (#29)
  * Handle backspace key in debug console 

 -- Sam Steele <sam.steele@gmail.com>  Sat, 2 Jun 2007 16:00:00 -0500

dreamzzt (3.0.6.1) stable; urgency=high

  * Pressing the enter key could crash the game (ticket #24)
  * Enemies no longer trigger touch events on ZZT-OOP scripts (ticket #25)
  * Allow capital letters and punctuation in DreamZZT Online passwords (ticket #26)

 -- Sam Steele <sam.steele@gmail.com>  Sat, 17 Feb 2007 16:00:00 -0500

dreamzzt (3.0.6) stable; urgency=low

  * Online leaderboard
  * On-the-fly board compression (ticket #6)
  * Integrated editor
  * Online version checking
  * Associate with ZZT and SAV files
  * New application and document icons
  * Use OS-provided file browser where available
  * New popup-window API
  * Digitized drum samples
  * Centipedes

  * Fix memory leaks and buffer overflows
  * Use reenter coordinates from board header (ticket #16)
  * Enable animated water in town.zzt
  * Fix a buffer overflow in the board title
  * Improve handling of pushing objects
  * Fix timing on duplicators
  * Prevent single-line status messages from opening TUIWindows
  * Many ZZT-OOP bug fixes
  * Fix a missing glyph in the ZZT font

 -- Sam Steele <sam.steele@gmail.com>  Mon,  29 Jan 2007 01:00:00 -0500

